===============================================================================
[02] PARTITIONING
=================

Screen title:
AOS INSTALLER - PARTITIONING

Purpose:
Choose how AOS should use the disk.

Detected disks:

[0] /dev/vda
[1] /dev/vdb
[2] /dev/sda

Selected disk: __________________________

Partitioning mode:

[1] Auto-partition selected disk
[2] Manual partitioning
[3] View disk information
[4] Back to main menu

---

AUTO-PARTITION MODE

Auto-partition will erase the selected disk and create the required AOS layout.

Default layout:

/dev/vda1    boot/root partition

WARNING:
Auto-partition will delete all data on the selected disk.

To continue, type:

AOS

Confirmation: __________________________

Auto-partition actions:

[1] Start auto-partition
[2] Cancel and go back

---

MANUAL PARTITIONING MODE

Manual partitioning opens the AOS partition command.

Command:

partition

Use this mode if you want to manually create, delete, or edit partitions.

After manual partitioning is complete, return to the installer and select the
partition where AOS should be installed.

Selected install partition: ______________

Manual partitioning actions:

[1] Open partition command
[2] Save selected partition
[3] Back to partitioning menu

